7755324,0.05133604,0.01838969,-0.06730562,0.00122146,0.08859148,-0.04739574,0.01413298,-0.00273896,0.07208260,-0.00022192,0.06465930,-0.04091947,0.03779692,0.01457667,-0.04404764,-0.01649688,0.00245460,-0.00508105,-0.04240117,-0.06078631,0.03396098,-0.02433770,-0.07080518,-0.06862932,-0.04301237,0.02629302,-0.00159787,-0.08422553,-0.00639866,0.00728176,0.02894001,-0.01635881,-0.09457886,-0.03127577,-0.10332593,0.02718465,0.07778031,0.05190769,0.08868407,-0.04874270,0.02438176]',E'Stream overriding\n\nOur `CacheInterceptor` has a hardcoded `isCached` variable and a hardcoded response `[]` as well. The key point to note is that we return a new stream here, created by the RxJS `of()` operator, therefore the route handler **won''t be called** at all. When someone calls an endpoint that makes use of `CacheInterceptor`, the response (a hardcoded, empty array) will be returned immediately. In order to create a generic solution, you can take advantage of `Reflector` and create a custom decorator','{"source": "nestjs", "version": "11", "language": "typescript", "title": "Interceptors", "section_title": "interceptors", "url": "https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/interceptors.md", "topics": "nestjs,typescript,interceptors", "categories": "web,typescript,rest,enterprise"}');
